Anker Nano is a great Fast Charger for your new iPhone:

• Blazing Fast speeds (20W) - 3X faster than the original 5W iPhone charger
• Ultra Compact Size 
• Lightweight and Portable
• More affordable than the Apple Chargers in most regions
• USB-C port 

@anker_official provided us with a review unit of the Anker Nano - not a paid post

You can get Anker Nano fast Charger for your new iPhone: https://amzn.to/34bTTzE

node.text:
Apple is expected to get rid of the Pacific Blue finish in the upcoming 12S Pro (not 12 as mentioned in the title) and replace it with another version of gold (could be rose gold or copper) while some say that we may finally see a red color. 

Other sources mention that a stealthier black version than the current Graphite finish could finally drop and stand next to the widely appraised matte black finish of the S21 Ultra. 

Which color would you like to see in the upcoming iPhone 13 Pro and Pro Max?

Fantastic render by @vovalenard - go check him out. 

Looking forward to hearing your thoughts.

MagSafe battery pack works as a regular Qi Wireless Charger that can wirelessly charge your AirPods Pro or any other iPhone that supports wireless charging. 

Images by @broz1k 

It does lack the magnetic snapping on any device apart from the iPhone 12 series. 

Does the price ($99), wireless charging speed (5W) or battery capacity (1,460 mAh) prohibit you from purchasing it?
